title: Trump’s new plan lets Americans 'buy their own healthcare’
description: US President Donald Trump discusses the health care plan, which lets people “buy their own healthcare”.  Mr Trump said, the money going to “insurance companies” should be “directly” going to Americans.  “They’ll get much better healthcare than they get wth the unaffordable.  “It’s a great solution to much better healthcare at a much lower cost.”

title: Trump attempts to drive Maduro ‘out of office’ without armed conflict using naval blockade
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker comments on America’s naval blockade of “sanctioned oil vessels” leaving and heading to Venezuela.  “President Trump is trying to ratchet up the pressure on Maduro to try to drive him out of office without armed conflict,” he told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “The last thing he wants to do is invade Venezuela. That’s not going to happen.”

title: Parliament won’t reconvene before Christmas: Anthony Albanese
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese declares Parliament won't reconvene before Christmas as it’s “not practical”.

title: ‘She was an embarrassment’: Kamala could run again in 2028 despite ‘slim and none’ chances
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker has reacted to an article by Axios about a potential 2028 run at the presidency by Kamala Harris again as she works to keep another White House campaign viable.  “Her chances are slim and none; she’s not going to be the Democrats’ nominee in 2028,” he told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “I mean, she was an embarrassment in 2024.”

title: ‘Demon Karen’ who berated Target employee for wearing Kirk shirt under workplace investigation
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi discusses an update on a “foul-mouthed demon Karen” following an “ugly, hate-filled” attack over a woman wearing a Charlie Kirk shirt.  “We played last night some really terrible footage, ugly, hate-filled footage of an attack against a lovely lady working at Target ... trying to do her job when she’s set upon by this foul-mouthed demon Karen who berates her for wearing a Charlie Kirk shirt,” she said.  Ms Panahi said the “crazy Karen” who posted the clip is now being investigated by her workplace who claimed they were “deeply concerned about the tenor of this post”.

title: CNN guest shockingly concedes Donald Trump has successfully lowered inflation
description: A CNN guest has shockingly admitted that US President Donald Trump has delivered on his promise to lower inflation.  Harvard Professor Ken Rogoff appeared on CNN’s News Central to admit that Trump’s strong inflation results are “positive news”.  Rogoff’s comments follow the latest reports released by the Labour Department that revealed inflation had eased to 2.7 per cent in November 2025.  Despite the increased scrutiny the White House has faced over how slowly the US economy has recovered, inflation initially sat at 3% in September 2025.  “I was surprised; it was a better number than anyone was expecting. Look, inflation’s been very high. It’s stayed high. It has not been coming down,” Rogoff said.  “People were expecting it to be above 3%. It was well below 3%. I mean, I think the president will take this as good news. The investors will think that interest rates will get cut more.”

title: Rita Panahi reacts to ‘doomsday-wench’ Greta Thunberg’s latest cause
description: Sky News Rita Panahi has reacted to “doomsday-wench” Greta Thunberg’s latest cause.

title: TV host blasts 'one-trick pony' Democrats for consistently bashing Trump
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has blasted the 'one-trick pony' Democrats for consistently bashing Donald Trump.

title: AOC sparks online roast after saying she’d ‘stomp’ JD Vance in 2028 election
description: United States Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez has expressed that she would “stomp” US Vice President JD Vance in the 2028 US presidential election.  Her remarks come after Newswire reported AOC lead Vance 51%-49% in a hypothetical 2028 poll.  The recent Verasight poll had 1,1511 registered voters, with AOC replying to it with a one-word tweet.  AOC dismissed the polling, saying they are “three years out” from the election, with anything changing the way it could go in 2028.  Many took to social media to roast AOC, blasting her comments and claiming Vance would win over her.

title: Netflix cancels its ‘woke garbage’ gay military series
description: Netflix has reportedly cancelled its gay military series called ‘Boots’ after the Pentagon labelled it “woke garbage”.  ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield claims despite the Pentagon’s criticism of the show, it was actually “kind of popular”.  “I mean, it had way more eyeballs than ‘With Love, Meghan’, so there are a lot of disappointed fans,” she told Sky News host Rita Panahi.

title: Minns uses ‘extraordinary powers not seen before’ to restrict public assemblies
description: New South Wales Premier Chris Minns introduces new police powers to restrict public assemblies.  “The government will act to ensure that we restrict the authorisation of public assembly during high-risk times,” Mr Minns said.  “A declaration must be called within 14 days of a terrorism designation being reached under the police powers act. It will be in order for four days, but can be extended for a further 14 days up to a period of three months.  “This is obviously extraordinary powers not seen before in any jurisdiction in the country.”

title: ‘Vile’: Michelle Obama cops furious backlash for making friends’ murder ‘about herself’
description: Former first lady Michelle Obama is facing backlash after appearing on Jimmy Kimmel’s show just hours after her friends Rob and Michele Reiner were found dead in their home.  She revealed that she and Barack were meant to have dinner with the couple on Sunday, only to discover they had been killed in their home.  ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield hit out at Michelle Obama over her appearance.  “Can you imagine going and sitting on Johnny Carson and yucking it up with a comedian and talking about your murdered friend? This is such vulgar behaviour,” she told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “Making the murder about herself? That’s absolutely vile.  “I just was so disgusted by this.”

title: Meghan brutally skewered after ‘breaking up’ with her father in letter and ‘reprimanding him’
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield has hit out at Meghan Markle for only sending a letter to her estranged father who’s in hospital following his amputation surgery.  “Meghan’s already walked away,” she told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “According to the Times, we’re finding out that Meghan formally breaks up with her father in this letter and reprimands him for his relationship with the media.”

title: Mamdani appointee resigns in disgrace after antisemitic online posts resurface
description: A high-profile Zohran Mamdani appointee has resigned after social media posts were unearthed revealing a series of antisemitic comments.  The online posts included rants about “money-hungry Jews” and defunding NYPD “piggies.”  Catherine Almonte Da Costa’s short-lived appointment fell apart after the Anti-Defamation League demanded answers from Mamdani’s team about the past antisemitic posts.  Da Costa, who was tapped as NYC’s next director of appointments, had several stereotype-laden posts from 2011 and 2012.

title: ​Albanese announces national gun buyback scheme in wake of Bondi terror attack
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese announces a national gun buyback scheme in the wake of the Bondi Beach terror attack.  “The largest buyback since the Howard government initiated one in 1996,” Mr Albanese said.  “We know that one of these terrorists held a firearm license and had six guns, despite living in the middle of Sydney’s suburbs.  “There’s no reason why someone in that situation needed that many guns.”
